    "body" : "<p>as for 07.2019 <a href=\"https://adoptopenjdk.net/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://adoptopenjdk.net/</a> has official Alpine support for Java 11:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p><a href=\"https://github.com/AdoptOpenJDK/openjdk-docker/blob/master/11/jdk/alpine/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://github.com/AdoptOpenJDK/openjdk-docker/blob/master/11/jdk/alpine/</a></p></li>\n<li><p><a href=\"https://hub.docker.com/r/adoptopenjdk/openjdk11\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://hub.docker.com/r/adoptopenjdk/openjdk11</a></p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>However, modules (<em>jmods</em>, <code>jlink</code>) still shall be considered when one assembles minimal application.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: <em>slim</em> images don't contain some modules (like <code>java.sql</code>) - they are excluded explicitly (<a href=\"https://github.com/AdoptOpenJDK/openjdk-docker/blob/21b8393b9c23f94d6921a56cce27b026537c6ca2/11/jdk/alpine/slim-java.sh#L233\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://github.com/AdoptOpenJDK/openjdk-docker/blob/21b8393b9c23f94d6921a56cce27b026537c6ca2/11/jdk/alpine/slim-java.sh#L233</a>)</p>\n"
